article.headline: Pacific 61, Long Beach St. 51
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- Demetrece Young had 16 points, four rebounds and three assists to lead Pacific to a 61-51 victory against Long Beach State on Saturday night. Sam Willard's 3-pointer and a four-point play by Young began a game-ending 16-8 run by the Tigers (18-10, 10-4 Big West). Willard had 12 points and seven rebounds. T.J. Robinson had 19 points and eight rebounds to lead Long Beach State (14-15, 7-8). The lead changed hands six times in the second half before Michael Nunnally's two free throws with nine minutes remaining gave Pacific the lead for good.
